37:23.140 --> 37:31.620
with some fondness you've been very kind in only mentioning the things that I'm
rather pleased about. I also had a great many failures in places where I know I

37:31.620 --> 37:44.500
should have done better and was not witty enough to perceive it at the time. But
as an agent I think I did manage to get a number of writers on a track that

37:44.500 --> 37:55.420
would have taken a little more time to discover by themselves and as an editor I
feel that I did give a good many writers either their first publication or their

37:55.420 --> 38:07.120
most visible publication and I take pleasure in that. Outside of that I think
it's pure drudgery. The only really pleasurable thing about it is finding

38:07.120 --> 38:14.260
something and printing it and giving it to an audience that might otherwise
either never have existed or never have got into print.

