39:52.660 --> 40:03.640
very good name but it's a sort of it's like a Roman standard it's a rallying
point it's where you find a cluster of things that you like Norman Spinrad I

40:03.640 --> 40:12.700
know feels very badly about it and so does Harlan Ellison and so do several
others but I don't share their particular hangups Okay and in respect to that

40:12.700 --> 40:20.680
business about science fiction being separate I think you said the awards to
this effect that science fiction is a special taste I suppose that means there's

40:20.680 --> 40:28.740
a special sort of person that would appreciate it or tend to read it Well I
think that science fiction makes more demands on the reader than most kinds of

40:28.740 --> 40:38.700
writing you have to be willing to stretch your imagination you have to be
willing to follow what is sometimes a pretty complex argument and it's helpful

40:38.700 --> 40:52.900
if you know something about the real world not just how to go to the A&P but
